Opening up an LLC has some major benefits for your business & can be used as a powerful wealth building tool:

📌You’ll get access to more funding & credit. Business Credit limits can be 5x-10x the amount you’ll get for personal credit
📌Simplicity for business structuring
📌Protection…an LLC can limit personal liability because an LLC is legally separate from its owners
📌 LLCs can always take advantage of “pass-through” taxation in which the LLC does not pay any LLC taxes or corporate taxes

Business Credit & Funding cheat code 💎

Set up a business bank account with local credit unions/banks. This is going to do 2 things for your business:

1. Local banks/credit unions are notorious for working with their customers. Some of them even like to work with businesses & industry types within a certain radius. This means LESS competition for you to get MORE money for your biz!

2. Having a business bank account helps establish the business’s “start date”. This helps build up something called a “bank rating” which on the back end will you guessed it… help you secure HIGHER FUNDING

Getting approved for business funding comes down to trusting the process:

- Understand what’s on your credit report (personal & business)
- Knowing which product works best for your business (business credit card, term loans, SBA loan, credit lines or combination)
- How your business is set-up (business name, SIC codes, LLC/S-corp classifications, etc)
-Not all funding is created equal. Each one is like a different tool to get the job done.
